pageContext.claim: “It's got to be of course an electric car even if it only goes what, 160 miles? What do you do, it's 160 miles? Darling, where do I get a charge? Where do I get a charge, darling?”
pageContext.analysis: Several models of electric cars have travel ranges beyond 160 miles. A Tesla Model S goes 265 miles and the Tesla Model X goes 295 miles. The Nissan Leaf, designed for city driving, has a range of 107 miles.
